definition: to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
life/fate/order or command/to assign a name, title etc

sentences.english: These ties among our people are the life blood of our emerging partnership.
sentences.chinese: 我们人民之间的纽带是我们新兴伙伴关系的生命力。

sentences.english: Only after one's ideas have endured the test of time can they have vitality.
sentences.chinese: 一个人的观点要经的起时间的考验才有生命力。

sentences.english: I think, evergreen, as air, will definitely be a strong vitality.
sentences.chinese: 我想，万年青那样神气，生命力一定会很强。

sentences.english: "Vitality Home" was always in disaster area after 512.
sentences.chinese: “生命力家园”在512地震之后一直扎根在灾区。

sentences.english: Anti-shock behavior of equipments on board the naval ship is a critical characteristic of the survivability.
sentences.chinese: 舰船设备抗冲击性能是舰船生命力设计的重要内容。

sentences.english: In this instance, the life-force refers to the Tathagatagarbha.
sentences.chinese: 在这种情况下，生命力是指如来藏。

sentences.english: Prana shakti, the life force, and manas shakti, the mental force, are the two fundamental creators.
sentences.chinese: 生命力和心理能量是两个最基本的造物者。

sentences.english: The seed vitality, sing songs from the poor not curse.
sentences.chinese: 生命力顽强的种子，从不对瘠土唱诅咒的歌。

sentences.english: Jngfang unceasingly send out new life energy in practice.
sentences.chinese: 经方在实践中不断焕发出新的生命力。

sentences.english: Almere is a city with vitality all of its own .
sentences.chinese: Almere它本身是一个城市以生命力全部。

sentences.english: We are all manifestations of the same life-force.
sentences.chinese: 我们都是同一生命力的明证。

sentences.english: The herbal complex of Lemon &Cedarwood balance oil production and restore vitality.
sentences.chinese: 柠檬和迷迭香平衡油脂分泌，使其恢复生命力。

sentences.english: Some very vital people belong to this blood-sucking type.
sentences.chinese: 某些生命力极旺盛的人便属于这吸血的一类。

sentences.english: The earth is reconstructing its tomorrow by its unbreakable power of life.
sentences.chinese: 地球用它摧枯拉朽的生命力，不断重塑着自己的明天。

sentences.english: The flourish of chattel hypothecation benefits from Anglo-American law.
sentences.chinese: 动产抵押制度重新焕发生命力得益于英美法系。

sentences.english: A life force indwells in nature.
sentences.chinese: 生命力永存于大自然中。

definition: opportunity to live/to reprieve from death/life force/vitality
to grow and multiply without end
